{
  "stem": "27285.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was really terrible because we were already once-- doesn't belonged to the Holocaust, but it is a Holocaust, we were already in the train and thrown out because Hitler had some meeting with Mussolini, or something--",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This I don't know, this I don't-- I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you can read it up somewhere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Anyway, and we were thrown back because there was a meeting of--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, the children, the whole--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not all the orphan-- all the children that had parents in Palestine were left behind-- with certificate to go to Palestine, legally.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, an attempt to take them via another time, another time, yes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my parents were already [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Until the war broke out there was a possibility of corresponding, and also, I think, through the Red Cross, once or twice.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I only remember that I wrote to my parents, with this Red Cross letter, which I can't, at the moment, find, that they should do something really fast because, otherwise, we won't meet.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you see, as a child you are so clever.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And unfortunately it was told they couldn't do anything, of course.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were without anything, they-- all they had was a rucksack, and a few books, and, as you saw already, my little Teddy bear, which is not so little, which I found after nine years, or eight years, here.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hello.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is my Teddy bear.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Anyway, that's the oldest thing left of my early, early, childhood, which I don't even know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He doesn't have a name, but he is-- like he was sitting there, in our little apartment in Vienna, and I found him again, in '46, when I came to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was very happy.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
